# Cursor rules — RentPilot AI

Read `AGENTS.md` at the repo root before making any changes.
It contains the mandatory issue-claiming protocol.

## Issue claiming (required before any code change)

1. Find a free issue:
   `gh issue list --state open --assignee "" | grep -v "in-progress"`
2. Claim it (all three commands):
   ```
   gh issue edit <N> --add-assignee @me
   gh issue edit <N> --add-label "in-progress"
   git checkout -b feat/<short-description> && git push -u origin feat/<short-description>
   ```
3. Release when PR is open:
   ```
   gh pr create ...
   gh issue edit <N> --remove-label "in-progress"
   ```

## Hard rules

- pnpm only (no npm, no yarn)
- Conventional Commits: `feat(scope): subject`
- All money as integer cents — use helpers in `src/lib/money.ts`
- All time stored as UTC — use helpers in `src/lib/time.ts`
- No un-redacted text to the decision LLM
- No direct push to main — all changes via PR
